{
    "problem": "Let $f(x)$ be a polynomial such that\n\\[f(x^2 + 1) = x^4 + 4x^2.\\]Find $f(x^2 - 1).$",
    "level": "Level 4",
    "type": "Intermediate Algebra",
    "solution": "Let $y = x^2 + 1.$  Then $x^2 = y - 1,$ and $x^4 = y^2 - 2y + 1,$ so\n\\[f(y) = (y^2 - 2y + 1) + 4(y - 1) = y^2 + 2y - 3.\\]Hence,\n\\[f(x^2 - 1) = (x^2 - 1)^2 + 2(x^2 - 1) - 3 = \\boxed{x^4 - 4}.\\]"
}